  "prompt": "Does Indian Institute of science provide plagiarism check for outsiders?",
  "response": "No, the Indian Institute of Science (IISc) generally does not offer plagiarism checking services for individuals or organizations outside of the institute. Their plagiarism detection tools and resources are primarily for internal use, for their students, faculty, and researchers to ensure academic integrity within their own research and publications.\n\nWhile you may find some universities or colleges in India offering plagiarism checking services to outsiders, IISc is not typically one of them.\n\nHere are some alternatives you can consider for plagiarism checking:\n\n*   **Commercial Plagiarism Checkers:** Services like Turnitin, iThenticate, Grammarly, and Copyscape are popular and widely used. Many offer free trials or have paid subscription plans.\n*   **University Services (in rare cases):** Some universities, although not typically IISc, may offer limited plagiarism checking services to external researchers for a fee. You could try contacting relevant departments at other universities directly.\n*   **Freelance Editors and Proofreaders:** Many freelance editors and proofreaders offer plagiarism checking as part of their services.\n*   **Free Online Plagiarism Checkers (Use with Caution):** There are many free online plagiarism checkers available, but be cautious about uploading sensitive documents to these sites as they may not have robust privacy policies. Also, the accuracy of these free tools can vary significantly.\n\nRemember to always review your work carefully and properly cite all sources to avoid plagiarism.\n",
